Class ChangedValueListener

java.lang.Object
ChangedValueListener
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.EventListener, javax.swing.event.DocumentListener
public class ChangedValueListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.swing.event.DocumentListener
Class implementing DocumentListener interface for Cell class. Main purpose of this class is to validate input for Cell class. Valid input is single digit of 1-9.
See Also:
Validator, Cell

    • changeText

      private void changeText()
      Method used to handle input validation. Uses runnable assist, that is invoked later by Swing event-dispatching thread, to validate input from player. Must be invoked later because of the errors that non-safe Swing data structures are causing. Uses Validator class, which methods simply return answer to question 'Is input valid?'.
